    "narrative": "The **Austin Waves** offense is primed for a high-ceiling performance today against several vulnerable arms, led by our standout play, **Gunnar Henderson**. With an efficiency score of 83.29, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive 15% boost due to a favorable matchup against Michael Wacha and an advantageous wind-out scenario. He is closely followed by **Kyle Tucker** (77.88) and **Jackson Merrill** (75.10), the latter of whom draws a massive 14% park factor boost at a hitters-friendly venue against Tomoyuki Sugano. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, **Nasim Nunez**, and **Brady House** all receive double-digit bumps from the exploitable 5.07 xERA of Didier Fuentes, making this trio essential for capturing the volume required for our 5x5 Roto climb.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Marcell Ozuna**, who just missed the cut with a 60.82 score. While **Marcell Ozuna** carries significant power potential, the optimizer prioritized the specific situational advantages of **Dominic Smith**, whose platoon edge and park factor outweighed the raw projection of our designated hitter. We are also monitoring the \"Lineup Pending\" status for all our starters, particularly for **Drake Baldwin** and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**, whose high scores are contingent on maintaining their projected spots in the two and three-hole respectively. While the weather outlook is generally stable, the heavy reliance on these pending lineups introduces some volatility; we will need to ensure **Luis Robert Jr.** and **Miguel Vargas** remain in their favorable top-of-the-order slots to justify their elite scoring projections against their respective left-handed matchups.",
